{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f9c404d5-f58e-43dd-ad27-10e234b1db96","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle event mappings** on `MauiAppBuilder`. In your `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs on Android OnPause\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs on Android OnStop\n        }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs on iOS DidEnterBackground\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Platform blocks are guarded by `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives.\n- Each platform exposes its native lifecycle names (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy`, `WillTerminate`, etc.).\n- This approach keeps all lifecycle hooks centralized rather than requiring custom platform `Activity`/`AppDelegate` subclasses.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a1a345d3-5a5c-42a7-9209-6f2fa60a6ce5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"9563:840A1:13EB5EC:1655984:6A067051"},"id":"f7b1d3f5-8b47-4bf3-b661-4571dde52ca8","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:01:13.936Z","parentId":"d4a05ff2-037f-46a8-8380-4034fa616622"}
